WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:35.744 --> 00:00:37.037 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
Hey. You, there.

00:00:37.120 --> 00:00:39.414 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU]
Hmm?

00:00:39.497 --> 00:00:42.375 position:50% align:center
Hello. That was
a good stenka in there.

00:00:42.459 --> 00:00:43.960 position:50% align:center
I'm impressed.

00:00:48.214 --> 00:00:50.133 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO] You're pretty
big for a Japanese guy.

00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:53.345 position:50% align:center
I can tell it's not just
the bulky clothes.

00:00:53.428 --> 00:00:55.305 position:50% align:center
Saichi Sugimoto.

00:00:55.388 --> 00:00:57.390 position:50% align:center
You a stenka fighter, too?

00:00:57.474 --> 00:01:01.853 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU]
Hmm. My name is Maiharu Gansoku.

00:01:01.936 --> 00:01:03.938 position:50% align:center
It isn't often you see
a Japanese man

00:01:04.022 --> 00:01:05.732 position:50% align:center
offering a handshake.

00:01:11.821 --> 00:01:15.658 position:50% align:center
Sugimoto. I'll see
you again very soon.

00:01:21.331 --> 00:01:22.749 position:50% align:center
Finally, there you are.

00:01:22.832 --> 00:01:25.585 position:50% align:center
So? What'd that guy want?

00:01:25.669 --> 00:01:26.920 position:50% align:center
Nothing.

00:03:02.307 --> 00:03:03.767 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] "The story of
the Japanese soldiers

00:03:03.850 --> 00:03:05.685 position:50% align:center
has spread quickly.

00:03:05.769 --> 00:03:07.937 position:50% align:center
According to the rumors,
they could even beat the man

00:03:08.021 --> 00:03:09.689 position:50% align:center
with the tattoos.

00:03:09.773 --> 00:03:12.442 position:50% align:center
As it happens, he'll be
at the stenka tonight.

00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:15.195 position:50% align:center
Many here will
bet on you," he says.

00:03:15.278 --> 00:03:17.405 position:50% align:center
He made it clear that
if we lose deliberately,

00:03:17.489 --> 00:03:19.199 position:50% align:center
he stands to win a lot of money.

00:03:19.282 --> 00:03:21.951 position:50% align:center
What about the deal from
before to give our dog back?

00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:24.162 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:03:24.245 --> 00:03:26.581 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] "You can have it
back when the match is over."

00:03:27.957 --> 00:03:29.376 position:50% align:center
[whimpering]

00:03:29.459 --> 00:03:32.045 position:50% align:center
I believe that some Ainu
punish offenses by slicing off

00:03:32.128 --> 00:03:34.172 position:50% align:center
a person's nose or ears.

00:03:34.255 --> 00:03:36.508 position:50% align:center
What about your people? Do they?

00:03:36.591 --> 00:03:38.134 position:50% align:center
We cut off their fingertips!

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:40.762 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:03:40.845 --> 00:03:43.014 position:50% align:center
And now he's saying if we do
that, he's going to tell the man

00:03:43.098 --> 00:03:45.225 position:50% align:center
with the tattoos
we're after him.

00:03:45.308 --> 00:03:47.018 position:50% align:center
You're playin' hardball
with the wrong guys.

00:03:47.102 --> 00:03:48.603 position:50% align:center
[BARTENDER 25A rasping]

00:03:48.687 --> 00:03:52.565 position:50% align:center
Right, listen up. Maybe now is
a good time to go over the plan.

00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:55.735 position:50% align:center
Tsukishima, make sure
you translate this.

00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:59.155 position:50% align:center
First, we slice off one finger
at a time until we get the dog.

00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.740 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME speaking Russian]

00:04:00.824 --> 00:04:02.283 position:50% align:center
[KOITO] Then, when we're done
burying him in the back yard,

00:04:02.367 --> 00:04:05.787 position:50% align:center
we go to the stenka and find
the man with the tattoos.

00:04:06.121 --> 00:04:07.372 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME speaking Russian]

00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:09.541 position:50% align:center
[KOITO] We don't do the stenka.
We kidnap the man

00:04:09.624 --> 00:04:13.003 position:50% align:center
and take him to the forest,
where we'll shoot him.

00:04:13.086 --> 00:04:20.010 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME speaking Russian]

00:04:20.093 --> 00:04:23.263 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:28.059 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:29.894 position:50% align:center
Index first.

00:04:29.978 --> 00:04:31.396 position:50% align:center
Hold his hand, Tsukishima.

00:04:31.479 --> 00:04:32.981 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
No, wait.

00:04:33.064 --> 00:04:35.233 position:50% align:center
Let's see if he actually
knows something first.

00:04:35.316 --> 00:04:37.318 position:50% align:center
[KOITO] Hmph. That would
be a waste of time.

00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:39.946 position:50% align:center
He's obviously lying,
so we won't kill him.

00:04:40.030 --> 00:04:43.241 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I agree.
We can't trust him.

00:04:43.324 --> 00:04:46.286 position:50% align:center
No point getting caught up in
more stenka bets because of him.

00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:48.621 position:50% align:center
There would be
nothing in that for us.

00:04:48.705 --> 00:04:50.707 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
This isn't like you, Sugimoto.

00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:53.418 position:50% align:center
You're usually a lot smarter.

00:04:53.501 --> 00:04:56.671 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
I'm sorry, Enonoka. But...

00:04:58.256 --> 00:05:00.133 position:50% align:center
If there's even the slightest
chance that doing this will

00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:04.512 position:50% align:center
lead us to Asirpa,
I can't waste that shot.

00:05:06.014 --> 00:05:07.891 position:50% align:center
[MEN yelling]

00:05:07.974 --> 00:05:10.602 position:50% align:center
[yelling in Russian]

00:05:10.685 --> 00:05:12.771 position:50% align:center
[RANDOM MAN 26B] I bet a lotta
money on you, Japanese!

00:05:12.854 --> 00:05:15.482 position:50% align:center
[RANDOM MAN 26C]
Come on, win for me, soldiers!

00:05:15.565 --> 00:05:18.610 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU growls]

00:05:18.693 --> 00:05:20.612 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
The code tattoos!

00:05:24.366 --> 00:05:26.117 position:50% align:center
It's self-expression.

00:05:26.201 --> 00:05:28.411 position:50% align:center
To me, stenka's no different
than expressing oneself

00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:31.456 position:50% align:center
through dance,
literature, or any fine art.

00:05:31.539 --> 00:05:35.543 position:50% align:center
I'll punch anyone
with this fist. Anyone.

00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:37.712 position:50% align:center
People choose how they wish
to be known to the world,

00:05:37.796 --> 00:05:40.131 position:50% align:center
and from the time I was
a child, my method of choice

00:05:40.215 --> 00:05:42.175 position:50% align:center
has been violence.

00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:45.512 position:50% align:center
Oddly, nobody's
ever liked me much.

00:05:45.595 --> 00:05:49.891 position:50% align:center
[sighs] It's because this world
has never understood me.

00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:53.603 position:50% align:center
I've spent most of
my life in prison.

00:05:53.687 --> 00:05:56.690 position:50% align:center
Probably explains
a lot. Although...

00:05:56.773 --> 00:06:00.360 position:50% align:center
Unlike most, I actually
enjoyed my time there.

00:06:00.443 --> 00:06:02.946 position:50% align:center
The prisons were
filled with violence.

00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:06.074 position:50% align:center
Everyone would cheer
when I punched a guard.

00:06:06.157 --> 00:06:08.368 position:50% align:center
And I met the most
wonderful people,

00:06:08.451 --> 00:06:11.079 position:50% align:center
but Ushiyama was the only
one strong enough to stop me

00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:12.872 position:50% align:center
with his bare hands.

00:06:12.956 --> 00:06:17.335 position:50% align:center
Once you grab someone
in judo, it's over.

00:06:17.419 --> 00:06:20.839 position:50% align:center
I wonder if they ever gave him
a woman as a reward?

00:06:20.922 --> 00:06:22.424 position:50% align:center
Any time I was out of control,

00:06:22.507 --> 00:06:26.011 position:50% align:center
Warden Inudou would
send Ushiyama after me.

00:06:26.094 --> 00:06:29.305 position:50% align:center
I was always happy to get
the chance to fight with him.

00:06:29.389 --> 00:06:31.141 position:50% align:center
And sometimes,
when it was just punching,

00:06:31.224 --> 00:06:33.059 position:50% align:center
I even managed to beat him!

00:06:33.143 --> 00:06:34.644 position:50% align:center
[PRISONERS cheering]

00:06:34.728 --> 00:06:37.063 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU] The moment I heard
those cheers was the moment

00:06:37.147 --> 00:06:40.775 position:50% align:center
I finally felt
accepted by society!

00:06:41.901 --> 00:06:43.028 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU moans]

00:06:43.111 --> 00:06:46.114 position:50% align:center
Hey, it's that man from before!

00:06:46.197 --> 00:06:49.534 position:50% align:center
Did you figure out he was
a tattooed prisoner?

00:06:49.617 --> 00:06:51.077 position:50% align:center
You kept it quiet.

00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:54.122 position:50% align:center
'Cause you wanted to face him
in the stenka, right?

00:06:54.205 --> 00:06:56.541 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
Then what about the fixed match?

00:06:56.624 --> 00:06:57.667 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
It doesn't look like you have

00:06:57.751 --> 00:07:00.045 position:50% align:center
any intention of losing.

00:07:00.128 --> 00:07:03.923 position:50% align:center
[KOITO] If you win, that chance
you talked about goes away.

00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:07.969 position:50% align:center
We're getting the dog, and we'll
get the info on Asirpa, too.

00:07:08.053 --> 00:07:09.721 position:50% align:center
Don't worry--I've
got a plan in mind

00:07:09.804 --> 00:07:11.514 position:50% align:center
that's gonna make
this all work out.

00:07:11.598 --> 00:07:13.475 position:50% align:center
So, we fight to win.

00:07:17.437 --> 00:07:19.147 position:50% align:center
[CIKAPASI]
It's the chatty Russian!

00:07:19.230 --> 00:07:21.941 position:50% align:center
Why isn't he at the stenka?
He's one of them!

00:07:22.025 --> 00:07:24.235 position:50% align:center
He's here to watch
the dog, I bet.

00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:26.571 position:50% align:center
I say we go get it
back on our own!

00:07:28.198 --> 00:07:30.867 position:50% align:center
[FIGHT ANNOUNCER 25A
speaking Russian]

00:07:32.994 --> 00:07:34.204 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO grunts]

00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:37.540 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:07:37.624 --> 00:07:39.292 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU]
Yeah, that's right!

00:07:39.376 --> 00:07:42.337 position:50% align:center
Tell me more!
Who is Sugimoto?!

00:07:43.963 --> 00:07:45.799 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO snarls]

00:07:45.882 --> 00:07:49.761 position:50% align:center
[grunting, groaning]

00:07:49.844 --> 00:07:51.054 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU groans]

00:07:52.889 --> 00:07:54.224 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:07:54.307 --> 00:07:58.436 position:50% align:center
Yes! Yes! Yes! Sugimoto!

00:08:00.647 --> 00:08:03.817 position:50% align:center
[MEN cheering]

00:08:08.738 --> 00:08:11.366 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO growls]

00:08:12.325 --> 00:08:13.618 position:50% align:center
[FIGHTER 26C groans]

00:08:16.663 --> 00:08:17.956 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU]
Hey! Stop!

00:08:18.039 --> 00:08:20.333 position:50% align:center
Pay attention to me, right now!

00:08:20.417 --> 00:08:23.211 position:50% align:center
Look at me! Look at me!
Look at me! Look at me!

00:08:23.294 --> 00:08:24.796 position:50% align:center
Look at me! Look
at me! Look at me!

00:08:24.879 --> 00:08:27.132 position:50% align:center
Look at me! Look!

00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:33.513 position:50% align:center
Hey, man, you okay?

00:08:33.596 --> 00:08:37.392 position:50% align:center
I... I don't... I, uh...

00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:43.273 position:50% align:center
[RANDOM MAN 26D]
They all went down 'cept

00:08:43.356 --> 00:08:44.482 position:50% align:center
the man with the tats!

00:08:44.566 --> 00:08:46.234 position:50% align:center
[RANDOM MAN 26E]
Get 'em, Japanese!

00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:50.155 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU sighs] Come at me!
I'll take all of you at once!

00:08:50.238 --> 00:08:51.614 position:50% align:center
[growling]

00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:52.949 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
You bastard!

00:08:54.325 --> 00:08:56.244 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU]
More... More!

00:08:56.327 --> 00:08:58.496 position:50% align:center
Yeah, gimme more!

00:08:58.580 --> 00:09:00.665 position:50% align:center
[groaning]

00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:05.712 position:50% align:center
[MEN cheering]

00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:07.213 position:50% align:center
He's so strong.

00:09:07.297 --> 00:09:08.882 position:50% align:center
He's too strong.

00:09:08.965 --> 00:09:12.635 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
No, I... I gotta...

00:09:12.719 --> 00:09:15.972 position:50% align:center
Here I am.
And now you know me.

00:09:19.476 --> 00:09:20.810 position:50% align:center
[gasping]

00:09:20.894 --> 00:09:23.188 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU groans]

00:09:23.271 --> 00:09:28.151 position:50% align:center
[yelling in Russian]

00:09:28.234 --> 00:09:30.111 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
Sugimoto, what are you doing?

00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:35.450 position:50% align:center
Oh, yes, now I get it! This is
your real plan, isn't it?

00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
Ahh!

00:09:37.035 --> 00:09:38.370 position:50% align:center
Calm down, Sugimo--

00:09:39.746 --> 00:09:41.790 position:50% align:center
[yelling in Russian]

00:09:50.173 --> 00:09:52.926 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
I am Immortal Sugimoto!

00:09:53.009 --> 00:10:00.016 position:50% align:center
[speaking in Russian]

00:10:02.185 --> 00:10:04.938 position:50% align:center
[Russian continues]

00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:06.272 position:50% align:center
Okay...

00:10:07.691 --> 00:10:10.735 position:50% align:center
I'm right! This really was
your plan, wasn't it?

00:10:13.029 --> 00:10:14.614 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
Ah.

00:10:14.698 --> 00:10:16.366 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Uh...

00:10:16.449 --> 00:10:18.284 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
Sugimoto?

00:10:18.368 --> 00:10:19.869 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO]
It's the Seventh.

00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.705 position:50% align:center
They're after me.

00:10:21.788 --> 00:10:23.915 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] Lieutenant Koito,
this isn't a plan!

00:10:23.998 --> 00:10:26.126 position:50% align:center
He just took too many
hits to the head!

00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:30.922 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:10:31.006 --> 00:10:32.841 position:50% align:center
[speaking Russian]

00:10:32.924 --> 00:10:34.718 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.929 position:50% align:center
[SUGIMOTO growls]
Give... gold!

00:10:38.013 --> 00:10:41.391 position:50% align:center
[gasps] After all we've
been through together,

00:10:41.474 --> 00:10:43.893 position:50% align:center
it's only about the tattoos?
That just hurts!

00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:45.437 position:50% align:center
Welp, truth's out!

00:10:45.520 --> 00:10:48.565 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU] I really thought
we might be able to connect!

00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:54.821 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
The unfortunate monster.

00:10:54.904 --> 00:10:56.364 position:50% align:center
Gansoku.

00:10:57.032 --> 00:10:59.451 position:50% align:center
[MEN screaming]

00:10:59.534 --> 00:11:00.994 position:50% align:center
Where'd he go?

00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:01.995 position:50% align:center
There!

00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:03.538 position:50% align:center
Follow him!

00:11:03.621 --> 00:11:05.999 position:50% align:center
But Sugimoto! What do we do?

00:11:06.082 --> 00:11:07.709 position:50% align:center
He's dangerous, leave him!

00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:09.377 position:50% align:center
We have to go
after the prisoner!

00:11:09.461 --> 00:11:14.758 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU panting]

00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:17.135 position:50% align:center
They followed me
all the way up here?

00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:19.387 position:50% align:center
I've got to get
out of this place.

00:11:22.015 --> 00:11:25.810 position:50% align:center
[growling]

00:11:25.894 --> 00:11:27.312 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
Where'd he go?

00:11:27.395 --> 00:11:28.813 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
Follow the footprints!

00:11:28.897 --> 00:11:29.981 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
It's too dark.

00:11:30.065 --> 00:11:31.066 position:50% align:center
And too cold.

00:11:31.149 --> 00:11:34.277 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU screams]

00:11:34.361 --> 00:11:38.656 position:50% align:center
[groaning]
Let me go!

00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:40.617 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI] That's him!
A wolverine's got him!

00:11:40.700 --> 00:11:43.036 position:50% align:center
Sergeant, quick!
Do you have a gun?

00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:44.621 position:50% align:center
Does it look like I do?

00:11:44.704 --> 00:11:47.082 position:50% align:center
We have to help,
it'll eat the tattoos!

00:11:47.165 --> 00:11:49.167 position:50% align:center
[screaming]

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:58.385 position:50% align:center
Run! We can't beat
that thing with stenka!

00:11:58.468 --> 00:11:59.386 position:50% align:center
[GANSOKU groans]

00:11:59.469 --> 00:12:01.012 position:50% align:center
[WOLVERINE growls]

00:12:03.306 --> 00:12:04.683 position:50% align:center
[KOITO]
A shack! Keep running!

00:12:04.766 --> 00:12:06.142 position:50% align:center
It'll catch up!

00:12:10.939 --> 00:12:12.607 position:50% align:center
[huffing]

00:12:14.734 --> 00:12:17.362 position:50% align:center
[sighs]
Hot!

00:12:17.445 --> 00:12:19.447 position:50% align:center
I know, I don't get it.

00:12:19.531 --> 00:12:20.740 position:50% align:center
A steam bath!

00:12:20.824 --> 00:12:22.075 position:50% align:center
It's a Russian thing!

00:12:22.158 --> 00:12:23.743 position:50% align:center
A banya!

00:12:23.827 --> 00:12:27.539 position:50% align:center
It's too much! We can't
stay here for very long!

00:12:27.622 --> 00:12:29.457 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME]
But the wolverine's outside!

00:12:29.541 --> 00:12:31.376 position:50% align:center
[growls]
What do we do?

00:12:32.877 --> 00:12:35.338 position:50% align:center
Everyone, think!

00:12:35.422 --> 00:12:38.925 position:50% align:center
[TANIGAKI]
I can't... Too hot.

00:12:39.009 --> 00:12:41.553 position:50% align:center
It's so hot!

00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:44.347 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Banya!

00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.702 position:50% align:center
[ENONOKA]
It's locked! What do we do?

00:13:07.537 --> 00:13:10.457 position:50% align:center
We'll shoot it with
Tanigaki Nispa's gun.

00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:12.625 position:50% align:center
[ENONOKA]
No! Gun is too loud!

00:13:14.711 --> 00:13:17.589 position:50% align:center
[HAJIME] Crap. That wolverine
won't give up.

00:13:17.672 --> 00:13:19.466 position:50% align:center
Anything we can use as a weapon?

